title: Top travel photos of the week
persons: ILYA NAYMUSHIN/REUTERS JON NAZCA/REUTERS JASON LEE/REUTERS
text:
Top travel photos of the week Last updated 10:12, August 28 2015 REUTERS ALEXANDRE MENEGHINI/REUTERS LUCAS JACKSON/REUTERS ALBERT GEA/REUTERS KIM HONG-JI/REUTERS CARLO ALLEGRI/REUTERS ALBERT GEA/REUTERS ALBERT GEA/REUTERS DAVID DEGNER/GETTY IMAGES REUTERS ADREES LATIF/REUTERS REGIS DUVIGNAU/REUTERS LUCAS JACKSON/REUTERS ROMEO RANOCO/REUTERS JON NAZCA/REUTERS EDGAR SU/REUTERS EDGAR SU/REUTERS ILYA NAYMUSHIN/REUTERS JON NAZCA/REUTERS JASON LEE/REUTERS DAVID RAMOS/GETTY IMAGES HANNAH PETERS/GETTY IMAGES SCOTT BARBOUR/GETTY IMAGES 
A street vendor sells Guy Fawkes masks at the Constitution Square in downtown Guatemala City, Guatemala 
Mechanic and salsa dance instructor Ariel Domninguez, 26, (L), gives a class to Jarman Frash, 25, a medical student from Germany in Havana. 
Tourists pose for photographs with a landmark statue of a bull in New York 
People cool off at platja d'Aro beach in Costa Brava, north of Barcelona, Spain. 
A tourist hangs a ribbon bearing messages wishing the unification of the two Koreas on a barbed-wire fence at the Imjingak pavilion near the demilitarized zone separating the two Koreas in Paju, South Korea. 
Robert Burck known as the original 'Naked Cowboy' carries a woman to pose for a photo while wearing his bikini top, which he is wearing due to the recent concerns of topless street performers in Times Square, in the Manhattan borough of New Yor 
People walk by Las Ramblas in Barcelona, Spain. 
A view of Sant Sebastia and Sant Miquel and Barceloneta beaches in Barceloneta neighborhood in Barcelona. 
A Bedouin guide walks across an empty damn in South Sinai near St. Catherine, Egypt. 
A family takes a selfie in front of sculptures of fiberglass horses in downtown Ciudad Juarez, Mexico. 
Revelers kiss on Bourbon Street, located in the French Quarter of New Orleans, Louisiana. 
Tourists gather on the grass near the fountains across the river from the Eiffel Tower on a warm summer's day in Paris. 
Tourists pose for photographs with a landmark statue of a bull in New York. 
A Buddhist monk offers prayers for the victims during the Day of Prayer ceremony of the fifth anniversary of the 2010 hostage crisis, at the Luneta Park in Manila. 
Women carry shopping bags at La Bola street in downtown Ronda, southern Spain. 
Women wearing kimonos look at the Singapore Flyer shrouded by haze near the central business district in Singapore. 
People watch the sun set near the skyline of the central business district shrouded by haze in Singapore. 
A boat sails along the Yenisei River in the Siberian Taiga area outside Krasnoyarsk, Russia. 
A jet flies past the moon over Ardales, near Malaga, southern Spain. 
A man cycles past Beijing's Tiananmen Gate on a sunny day. 
Revellers enjoy the atmosphere in tomato pulp while participating the annual Tomatina festival in Bunol, Spain. 
Teal Harle of Canada competes in the FIS Freestyle Ski World Cup Slopestyle Qualification during the Winter Games NZ at Cardrona Alpine Resort 
Fans in the crowd let off flares during the FFA Cup between Heidelberg United and Sydney United 58 FC at Olympic Village in Melbourne, Australia. 1 of 23 « Previous « Previous Next » Next » 
From a sunny, crowded beach in Barcelona to the "Naked Cowboy" in Times Square, here is our round up of the top travel photos from around the world. 
Do you have a favourite? Let us know in the comments. Out of this world travel pics Share your stories, photos and videos. LUCAS JACKSON/REUTERS
